== Semi-protected edit request on 17 November 2014 ==
{{edit semi-protected|Romanian presidential election, 2014|answered=y}} <!-- Begin request --> Please re-up the picture of Mr Klaus Iohannis on the right-hand side of the screen, as it appears the someone deleted it, leaving only Mr Victor Ponta's picture, who happens to in fact have lost the elections according to all preliminary results and statistical agencies. == Please add Chicago/Niles, IL under diaspora ==
There aren't any U.S. cities listed under the diaspora. In Niles, IL, one of the two voting locations in the Chicago area, waits were enormous. Officials had only 4 stamps for people to use. It was complete disorganization. Adding Chicago/Niles, IL to the list shows that Romanians are not only living abroad throughout Europe, but also in large numbers in the U.S.
== Please change references to Socialist Alliance Party to Socialist Alternative Party ==
The party changed its name in December 2013 - see the Wikipedia article on it. "Socialist Alliance Party" now redirects to "Socialist Alternative Party".
